The paper discusses a physical model for lidar sensors that can be used for mapping and localization in unstructured environments. This is a core topic in robotics, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of probabilistic state estimation approaches, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for sensor fusion and localization. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed model in real-world experiments, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, lidar sensors are often used in autonomous vehicles, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
